result.name: sfa-course-directory
result.notes:
The course directory contains information on courses offered by learning providers who are contracted with the Education and Skills Funding Agency (ESFA).

The directory contains information from over 2,900 organisations including colleges, schools, training providers and local education authorities. The file is updated monthly. 

Courses featured include adult further education, adult community learning, and courses aimed at people aged 16 to 18.

organization.name: education-funding-agency
organization.title: Education and Skills Funding Agency
organization.description:
The ESFA brings together the former responsibilities of the Education Funding Agency (EFA) and Skills Funding Agency (SFA) to create a single agency accountable for funding education and skills for children, young people and adults.

ESFA is an executive agency, sponsored by the Department for Education.
